title: Vote: Councilman to become Memphis' 1st white mayor since 91
text: > Top News Vote: Councilman to become Memphis' 1st white mayor since 91 FILE - In this Friday, Sept. 25, 2015 file photo, Memphis Mayor A C Wharton Jr. holds a campaign sign on a street corner in Memphis, Tenn. Wharton Jr. has conceded Memphis' mayoral election to a city council member who is now poised to become the city's first white mayor in almost a quarter-century. Wharton's concession to councilman Jim Strickland came late Thursday, Oct. 8, before complete results for the nonpartisan election were posted. (AP Photo/Adrian Sainz)
